It helped me immensely when I realized<p><pre><code>    obj.method();
</code></pre>
is a sugar for<p><pre><code>    obj.method.call(obj);
</code></pre>
Similarly, this picture helped me understand `bind`:<p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/StZOr.png" rel="nofollow">http://i.stack.imgur.com/StZOr.png</a><p>The a-ha moment for JS is when you realize it&#x27;s a <i>way</i> simpler language than you thought it was.
